  <h1>
   physics_particle_get_max_count
  </h1>
  With this function you can find out what the current cap value is on particles permitted in the physics simulation (you can set this value using
  <a href="physics_particle_set_max_count.htm">
   <span>
    physics_particle_set_max_count()
   </span>
  </a>
  ).
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">physics_particle_get_max_count()
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Real
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">if (physics_particle_count() &amp;amp;lt; physics_particle_get_max_count())
{
    physics_particle_create(0, x, y, 0, 0, c_white, 1, 1)
}
</code></pre>
  The above code will check to see if there are less than the maximum number of permitted particles in the room, and if so create one more.
 </body>
</html>